<span id="freeTextContainer11350164724843560441">I picked up this collection of Raymond Carver stories after watching the movie &quot;Birdman,&quot; which features a play based on the title story. <br/><br/>When I finished reading it, I was both impressed at Carver&apos;s brisk dialogue and wishing there had been more. He sketches scenes well, dances around a topic, reaches for an emotional peak, and then closes. <br/><br/>Like most short stories, it&apos;s a marvel of efficiency. But I still wish there had been more heft.</span>
  <span id="freeText11350164724843560441" style="display:none">I picked up this collection of Raymond Carver stories after watching the movie "Birdman," which features a play based on the title story. <br /><br />When I finished reading it, I was both impressed at Carver's brisk dialogue and wishing there had been more. He sketches scenes well, dances around a topic, reaches for an emotional peak, and then closes. <br /><br />Like most short stories, it's a marvel of efficiency. But I still wish there had been more heft.</span>
